  sessions: Map[SessionId, Session]
) {
  def add(s: Session): Sessions = 
    copy(sessions = sessions.updated(s.id, s))
}
```

**Scala case classes**:
- âœ… Immutable by default
- âœ… Have copy() for updates
- âœ… Can have methods
- âœ… Pattern matching support
- âœ… No need for separate "manager" trait

